<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<sec id="Sec9" class="sec">
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">C-Haines formulation</div>
 <p id="Par25" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The C-Haines index (CH) is formulated from two components, CA and CB
  <span class="sup">
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR4" href="#CR4">4</a>,
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR8" href="#CR8">8</a>
  </span>, as shown by Equations 
  <a rid="Equ1" ref-type="" href="#Equ1">1</a>–
  <a rid="Equ4" ref-type="" href="#Equ4">4</a>. CA is the Stability Score based on the temperature difference T850 – T700, where T850 and T700 are the temperatures at 850 hPa and 700 hPa, respectively. CB is the Humidity Score based on the 850 hPa dew point depression (DD850): equal to T850 – DP850, where DP850 is the dew point temperature at 850 hPa.
  <div id="Equ1" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">1</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${\rm{CA}}=0.5\,\ast \,({\rm{T}}850-{\rm{T}}700-4)$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M2" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CA</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">0.5</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mo">∗</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span stretchy="true" class="mo">(</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">T</span>
       <span class="mn">850</span>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">T</span>
       <span class="mn">700</span>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">4</span>
      </div>
      <span stretchy="true" class="mo">)</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="41598_2019_46362_Article_Equ1.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
  <div id="Equ2" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">2</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M3" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${\rm{CB}}=0.3333\,\ast \,({\rm{DD}}850-3),{\rm{with}}\,{\rm{DD850}}\,{\rm{limited}}\,{\rm{to}}\,{\rm{a}}\,{\rm{maximum}}\,{\rm{of}}\,{\rm{30}}\,^\circ C$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M4" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CB</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">0.3333</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mo">∗</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span stretchy="true" class="mo">(</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">DD</span>
       <span class="mn">850</span>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">3</span>
      </div>
      <span stretchy="true" class="mo">)</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">with</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">DD850</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">limited</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">to</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">a</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">maximum</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">of</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mn">30</span>
     <span width=".1em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mo">°</span>
     <span class="mi">C</span>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="41598_2019_46362_Article_Equ2.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
  <div id="Equ3" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">3</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M5" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${\rm{if}}\,{\rm{CB}} &gt; 5,{\rm{then}}\,{\rm{CB}}=5+0.5\,\ast \,({\rm{CB}}-5)$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M6" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">if</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CB</span>
     <span class="mo">&gt;</span>
     <span class="mn">5</span>
     <span class="mo">,</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">then</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CB</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span class="mn">5</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span class="mn">0.5</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <span class="mo">∗</span>
     <span width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span stretchy="true" class="mo">(</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CB</span>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mn">5</span>
      </div>
      <span stretchy="true" class="mo">)</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="41598_2019_46362_Article_Equ3.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
  <div id="Equ4" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">4</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M7" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${\rm{CH}}={\rm{CA}}+{\rm{CB}}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M8" display="block" class="math">
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CH</span>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CA</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
     <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">CB</span>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="41598_2019_46362_Article_Equ4.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par26" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">CH is calculated throughout this study using 0600 UTC values as provided by the various data sources, as this most closely aligns with mid-afternoon conditions in Australia, which is when dangerous fire activity most commonly occurs.</p>
</sec>
